  m_Name: Moby Dick
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  bookTitle: Moby Dick (Herman Melville)
  coverImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 552ef8a2a8c3b8c4688a565f65df80b2, type: 3}
  worldIcon: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 552ef8a2a8c3b8c4688a565f65df80b2, type: 3}
  pageContent: '"...The sea rose up as a giant white hump surfaced above the waves.
    Ahab stood at the bow of the whaleboat, gripping the harpoon so tightly his knuckles
    turned white. The whale struck with its tail, turning the boat into splinters.
    In this chaos of foam and fury, it became clear: this was not just a hunt for
    a beast, it was a man''s struggle with fate itself. The water around turned red,
    but the monster dove deep again, dragging fragments of ropes and hope with it..."'
